00:13:57.070 --> 00:13:59.160
But the rest, they're
all pretty much the same.

00:13:59.160 --> 00:14:01.800
So that's just one kind of
difference that we can look at.

00:14:01.800 --> 00:14:04.260
And if we looked over
the whole genome,

00:14:04.260 --> 00:14:06.840
we find that this
amount of difference

00:14:06.840 --> 00:14:09.240
is actually quite
representative of what we see

00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:11.460
over the whole DNA comparison.

00:14:11.460 --> 00:14:17.030
So that's about 1% different,
or 99% the same, you could say.

00:14:17.030 --> 00:14:19.510
But that's just one way of
counting the differences.

00:14:19.510 --> 00:14:20.790
There are actually other
