00:14:24.990 --> 00:14:25.830
OK, over here.

00:14:25.830 --> 00:14:27.060
Yeah.

00:14:27.060 --> 00:14:31.470
So in this loop here, so
that's the human sequence

00:14:31.470 --> 00:14:34.620
going across the top; chimpanzee
sequence across the bottom.

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:36.830
And there's this bit that's
looping out in human.

00:14:36.830 --> 00:14:40.110
There's nothing to match it
against on the other side.

00:14:40.110 --> 00:14:43.050
So there's a piece
of DNA that's either

00:14:43.050 --> 00:14:45.990
been inserted into
the human genome,

00:14:45.990 --> 00:14:48.240
or deleted from the
chimpanzee genome.

00:14:48.240 --> 00:14:50.250
But we can't match those up.

00:14:50.250 --> 00:14:52.590
And there are other bits
like that around the genome,

00:14:52.590 --> 00:14:54.360
if we were to do the
whole comparison.

00:14:54.360 --> 00:14:58.350
And that adds about
another 3% different.

00:14:58.350 --> 00:15:01.350
So if we put these together,
we get it's about 4%

00:15:01.350 --> 00:15:03.475
different, or 96% the same.

00:15:03.475 --> 00:15:05.850
It's the kind of thing you
