on the outside that we call

00:46:10.460 --> 00:46:11.960
the neocortex.

00:46:11.960 --> 00:46:14.220
And we've scaled
it to body size.

00:46:14.220 --> 00:46:17.885
So this must be an animal with a
very small amount of neocortex.

00:46:17.885 --> 00:46:20.010
And then this must be an
animal with a large amount

00:46:20.010 --> 00:46:21.590
of neocortex.

00:46:21.590 --> 00:46:25.400
Underneath these cubes that
represent different brain size,

00:46:25.400 --> 00:46:26.960
we've got a clue
as to what it is

00:46:26.960 --> 00:46:29.000
that's driving brain
size increases,

00:46:29.000 --> 00:46:31.443
or explaining brain
size increases.

00:46:31.443 --> 00:46:33.860
So what I'd like you to do is
lift up each of these cubes,

00:46:33.860 --> 00:46:38.360
and will reveal a
score for each species.

00:46:38.360 --> 00:46:39.260
Here we go, then.

