00:46:49.235 --> 00:46:52.110
A very cute type of primate.

00:46:52.110 --> 00:46:52.610
OK.

00:46:52.610 --> 00:46:53.970
What about this species here?

00:46:53.970 --> 00:46:56.390
Let's review the
score for this one.

00:46:56.390 --> 00:46:57.740
Oh, that's a lot.

00:46:57.740 --> 00:47:00.620
That's 17-- I can
count very quickly--

00:47:00.620 --> 00:47:02.240
small cubes.

00:47:02.240 --> 00:47:06.100
And this species
is a spider monkey.

00:47:06.100 --> 00:47:07.160
What about this one?

00:47:07.160 --> 00:47:08.650
What's the score for that one?

00:47:08.650 --> 00:47:12.250
Oh, 54 small cubes.

00:47:12.250 --> 00:47:15.420
This one is a chimpanzee.

00:47:15.420 --> 00:47:19.110
And then finally, would you
like to lift that big cube?

00:47:19.110 --> 00:47:21.210
There's a pile of
people underneath it.

00:47:21.210 --> 00:47:21.915
This is a human.

00:47:25.822 --> 00:47:26.780
And what these scores--

00:47:26.780 --> 00:47:30.390
[LAUGHTER]

00:47:30.390 --> 00:47:32.430
--what these scores
represent, Jasmine,

00:47:32.430 --> 00:47:36.610
is the size of social group that
these animals normally live in.

00:47:36.610 --> 00:47:39.520
So the slow loris is a
very solitary creature.

00:47:39.520 --> 00:47:41.100
It doesn't have any friends.

00:47:41.100 --> 00:47:42.600
It just lives on its own.

00:47:42.600 --> 00:47:45.450
Spider monkeys are a
little bit more gregarious.

00:47:45.450 --> 00:47:48.840
They live in a social
group which averages 17.

00:47:48.840 --> 00:47:53.370
Chimpanzees even more--
average group size of 54.

00:47:53.370 --> 00:47:57.860
Humans, on average
we have 150 friends.

00:47:57.860 --> 00:47:59.320
And that's not
just acquaintances.

00:47:59.320 --> 00:48:01.230
That's people we
know pretty well.

00:48:01.230 --> 00:48:04.800
Jasmine, thank you for revealing
the secret of big human brains.

00:48:04.800 --> 00:48:06.736
Thank you very much.

